\[BD = \sqrt{AB^2 - AD^2} = \sqrt{(5 - 0)^2 + (\sqrt{32} - \sqrt{27})^2}.\]By the Pythagorean theorem on right triangle $BCD,$
\[CD = \sqrt{BC^2 - BD^2} = \sqrt{(9 - 5)^2 + (3 - \sqrt{32})^2 - [(5 - 0)^2 + (\sqrt{32} - \sqrt{27})^2]}.\]Then
\begin{align*}
AC &= \sqrt{(9 - 0)^2 + (2 - \sqrt{27})^2 + 3^2} \\
&= \sqrt{9^2 + 2^2 + 3^2 - 2 \cdot 9 \cdot \sqrt{27} + 2 \cdot 2 \cdot \sqrt{27}} \\
&= \sqrt{94 - 12 \sqrt{27}}.
